  "english": [
    "<b>One who washes his hands</b> should <b>not recite <i>kiddush</i></b> after washing, as this would constitute an interruption between washing and eating, and he will have to wash again. Instead, he should hear <i>kiddush</i> from someone else. <b>Rav Yitzḥak bar Shmuel bar Marta said to them: Not</b> a lot of time has <b>yet</b> passed since <b>Rav died,</b> and <b>we have</b> already <b>forgotten his</b> halakhic <b>rulings. Many times I stood before Rav</b> and saw that <b>sometimes he preferred bread,</b> and <b>he would recite <i>kiddush</i> over bread.</b> On those occasions Rav would wash his hands, recite <i>kiddush</i> over the bread, and eat it. <b>At</b> other <b>times he preferred wine</b> and <b>would recite <i>kiddush</i> over wine.</b> This shows that <i>kiddush</i> is not considered an interruption between washing one’s hands and eating bread.",
    "<b>Rav Huna said</b> that <b>Rav said:</b> One who has <b>tasted</b> any food on Shabbat night may <b>not recite <i>kiddush</i></b> anymore that night, as one must recite <i>kiddush</i> before he eats. Instead, he recites <i>kiddush</i> during the day before the meal. <b>Rav Ḥana bar Ḥinnana raised a dilemma before Rav Huna:</b> If one <b>tasted</b> food at the conclusion of Shabbat before reciting <i>havdala</i>, <b>what is</b> the <i>halakha</i> with regard <b>to</b> whether <b>he</b> may <b>recite <i>havdala</i>? He said to him: I say</b> that one who has <b>tasted</b> food may still <b>recite <i>havdala</i>. And Rav Asi said:</b> One who has <b>tasted</b> food may <b>not recite <i>havdala</i>.</b>",
    "The Gemara relates that <b>Rav Yirmeya bar Abba happened to</b> come to <b>the house of Rav Asi. He forgot and tasted some</b> food after Shabbat before <i>havdala</i>. <b>They gave him a cup and he recited <i>havdala</i>.</b> Later, Rav Asi’s <b>wife said to</b> her husband: <b>But</b> my <b>Master does not act this way.</b> In your opinion, one who eats before <i>havdala</i> does not recite <i>havdala</i>. <b>He said to her: Leave</b> Rav Yirmeya bar Abba. <b>He maintains in accordance with</b> the opinion of <b>his rabbi.</b> Rav Yirmeya bar Abba was a student of Rav, who ruled that even one who has eaten may recite <i>havdala</i>.",
    "<b>Rav Yosef said</b> that <b>Shmuel said:</b> One who has <b>tasted</b> food before <i>kiddush</i> may <b>not recite <i>kiddush</i>,</b> and <b>one who has tasted</b> food before <i>havdala</i> may <b>not recite <i>havdala</i>. And Rabba said</b> that <b>Rav Naḥman said</b> that <b>Shmuel said:</b> One who has <b>tasted</b> may nevertheless <b>recite <i>kiddush</i>, and one who has tasted</b> may likewise <b>recite <i>havdala</i>.</b>"
  ],
  "gemara": [
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"0\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>הַנּוֹטֵל יָדָיו לֹא יְקַדֵּשׁ. אֲמַר לְהוּ רַב יִצְחָק",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "בַּר שְׁמוּאֵל בַּר מָרְתָא: אַכַּתִּי לָא נָח נַפְשֵׁיהּ",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "דְּרַב שְׁכַחְנִינְהוּ לִשְׁמַעְתְּתֵיהּ. זִמְנִין סַגִּיאִין",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "הֲוָה קָאֵימְנָא קַמֵּיהּ דְּרַב, זִימְנִין דַּחֲבִיבָא עֲלֵיהּ רִיפְתָּא —",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מְקַדֵּשׁ אַרִיפְתָּא. זִימְנִין דַּחֲבִיבָא לֵיהּ חַמְרָא —",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מְקַדֵּשׁ אַחַמְרָא. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"1\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אָמַר רַב הוּנָא אָמַר רַב:",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "טָעַם אֵינוֹ מְקַדֵּשׁ. בְּעָא מִינֵּיהּ רַב חָנָא בַּר",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "חִינָּנָא מֵרַב הוּנָא: טָעַם מַהוּ שֶׁיַּבְדִּיל? אֲמַר לֵיהּ, אֲנִי",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אוֹמֵר: טָעַם — מַבְדִּיל, וְרַב אַסִּי אָמַר: טָעַם — אֵינוֹ",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מַבְדִּיל. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"2\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>רַב יִרְמְיָה בַּר אַבָּא אִיקְּלַע לְבֵי רַב אַסִּי,",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אִישְׁתְּלִי וְטָעִים מִידֵּי, הַבוּ לֵיהּ כָּסָא וְאַבְדֵּיל.",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אֲמַרָה לֵיהּ דְּבֵיתְהוּ: וְהָא מָר לָא עָבֵיד הָכִי!",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אֲמַר לַהּ: שִׁבְקֵיהּ, כְּרַבֵּיהּ סְבִירָא לֵיהּ. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"3\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אָמַר",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "רַב יוֹסֵף אָמַר שְׁמוּאֵל: טָעַם — אֵינוֹ מְקַדֵּשׁ, טָעַם —",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אֵינוֹ מַבְדִּיל. וְרַבָּה אָמַר רַב נַחְמָן",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אָמַר שְׁמוּאֵל: טָעַם — מְקַדֵּשׁ, וְטָעַם — מַבְדִּיל.",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    }
  ],
  "rashi": [
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>הַנּוֹטֵל יָדָיו לֹא יְקַדֵּשׁ.</b> דקידושא מפסיק בין נטילה לאכילה והוי כהיסח",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 106b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "הדעת ובעי נטילה אחריתי בתר קידושא: <b>דחביבא</b> <b>ליה</b> <b>ריפתא.</b> שהיה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 106b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "רעב מקדש אריפתא אלמא לא בעי נטילה אחריתי אלא מעיקרא משי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 106b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ואכיל נהמא דקידושא: <b>דחביבא</b> <b>ליה</b> <b>חמרא.</b> שהיה צמא: <b>טעם.</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 106b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "אם אכל שוב אינו מקדש כל הלילה:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 106b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>אִישְׁתְּלִי</b> רב ירמיה: <b>אמרה</b> <b>ליה</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 106b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>דְּבֵיתְהוּ</b> דרב אסי לרב אסי: <b>והא</b> <b>מר</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 106b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>לָא עָבֵיד הָכִי.</b> דאמר רב אסי טעם",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 106b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "אינו מבדיל: <b>כרביה.</b> כרב דרב הונא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 106b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "משמיה דרב הוה אמר שמעתתיה:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 106b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
